  "mermaid": "graph TD\n    A[DNA Damage Event] --> B{Lesion Type?}\n    \n    B -->|UV Damage| C[Cyclobutane Pyrimidine Dimers]\n    B -->|UV Damage| D[6-4 Photoproducts]\n    B -->|Chemical Adduct| E[Bulky DNA Adducts]\n    B -->|Oxidative| F[Other Helix-Distorting Lesions]\n    \n    C --> G[Major Helix Distortion]\n    D --> G\n    E --> G\n    F --> G\n    \n    %% Damage Recognition Pathway Choice\n    G --> H{Repair Pathway?}\n    \n    H -->|Transcription-Coupled| I[RNA Pol Stalled at Lesion]\n    H -->|Global Genome| J[UvrA-UvrB Complex Formation]\n    \n    %% Transcription-Coupled NER\n    I --> K[Mfd Transcription Repair Coupling Factor]\n    K --> L[RNA Pol Displacement]\n    L --> M[Mfd Recruitment of UvrA]\n    M --> J\n    \n    %% Global Genome NER - Damage Recognition\n    J --> N[UvrA2-UvrB1 Complex]\n    N --> O[ATP-Dependent DNA Scanning]\n    O --> P{Damage Detected?}\n    \n    P -->|No Damage| Q[Continue Scanning]\n    Q --> O\n    P -->|Potential Damage| R[UvrB Loading]\n    \n    R --> S[UvrB DNA Unwinding]\n    S --> T[\u03b2-Hairpin Insertion]\n    T --> U{Damage Verification?}\n    \n    U -->|False Positive| V[UvrA-UvrB Dissociation]\n    V --> O\n    U -->|True Damage| W[Stable UvrB-DNA Complex]\n    \n    %% UvrA Dissociation and UvrC Recruitment\n    W --> X[ATP Hydrolysis]\n    X --> Y[UvrA Dissociation]\n    Y --> Z[UvrB Remains Bound]\n    \n    Z --> AA[UvrC Recognition of UvrB]\n    AA --> AB{UvrC Recruitment?}\n    AB -->|Yes| AC[UvrB-UvrC Complex]\n    AB -->|No| AD[Abortive Repair]\n    \n    %% Dual Incision\n    AC --> AE{Incision Coordination?}\n    AE -->|Both Sites Ready| AF[Dual Incision]\n    \n    AF --> AG[UvrC 3' Incision]\n    AG --> AH[4-5 nt 3' to Lesion]\n    AH --> AI[UvrC 5' Incision]\n    AI --> AJ[8 nt 5' to Lesion]\n    \n    AJ --> AK[12-13 nt Fragment Generated]\n    AK --> AL[UvrC Dissociation]\n    \n    %% Excision and Gap Creation\n    AL --> AM[UvrD Helicase Recognition]\n    AM --> AN{UvrD Activity?}\n    AN -->|ATP Available| AO[Helicase Unwinding]\n    AN -->|No ATP| AP[Stalled State]\n    \n    AO --> AQ[5' to 3' Translocation]\n    AQ --> AR[Oligonucleotide Displacement]\n    AR --> AS[Excised Fragment Release]\n    AS --> AT[UvrB Dissociation]\n    \n    AT --> AU[Single-Strand Gap 12-13 nt]\n    AU --> AV{Gap Filling Ready?}\n    \n    %% DNA Synthesis\n    AV -->|3'-OH Present| AW[DNA Pol I Recognition]\n    AV -->|End Processing Needed| AX[Additional Factors]\n    \n    AW --> AY[Pol I 5'-3' Polymerase]\n    AY --> AZ[dNTP Incorporation]\n    AZ --> BA[Processive Synthesis]\n    BA --> BB[Gap Filled 12-13 nt]\n    \n    BB --> BC{Nick Remaining?}\n    BC -->|Yes| BD[DNA Ligase Recognition]\n    BC -->|No| BE[Unexpected State]\n    \n    %% Nick Sealing\n    BD --> BF[NAD+ Ligase LigA]\n    BF --> BG[Adenylate Transfer]\n    BG --> BH[Phosphodiester Bond Formation]\n    BH --> BI[Nick Sealed]\n    \n    BI --> BJ[Restored DNA Helix]\n    BJ --> BK{Repair Verification?}\n    BK -->|Successful| BL[Genome Integrity]\n    BK -->|Residual Damage| BM[Secondary Repair]\n    \n    %% Quality Control\n    BL --> BN[Normal DNA Structure]\n    BN --> BO[Replication Competent]\n    BO --> BP[Transcription Competent]\n    BP --> BQ[Cell Survival]\n    \n    %% Error Pathways\n    AD --> BR[Incomplete Repair]\n    AP --> BR\n    BE --> BR\n    BM --> BS{Lesion Persistent?}\n    BS -->|Yes| BT[Alternative Repair Pathways]\n    BS -->|Bypass| BU[Translesion Synthesis]\n    \n    BT --> BV[Recombination Repair]\n    BU --> BW[Error-Prone Bypass]\n    \n    %% Regulation and Coordination\n    AX --> BY{Processing Type?}\n    BY -->|3' Block| BZ(\\1)\n    BY -->|5' Block| CA(\\1)\n    BZ --> AV\n    CA --> AV\n    \n    %% Final Outcomes\n    BQ --> CB[Successful NER]\n    BV --> CC[Backup Repair]\n    BW --> CD[Mutagenic Outcome]\n    \n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n    