  "name": "Nucleotide Excision Repair (NER)",
  "notGates": 0,
  "notes": "Comprehensive model of E. coli nucleotide excision repair including both global genome and transcription-coupled sub-pathways. The UvrABC system is the bacterial paradigm for bulky lesion repair, structurally and mechanistically distinct from eukaryotic NER. Essential for publication as demonstrates complex multi-protein coordination with 4 AND gates and sophisticated damage recognition logic.",
  "organism": "E. coli",
  "relatedProcesses": [
    "ecoli_base_excision_repair",
    "ecoli_mismatch_repair",
    "ecoli_sos_response",
    "ecoli_transcription_regulation"
  ],
  "scientificAccuracy": "This flowchart is based on decades of biochemical and genetic studies of the E. coli UvrABC system. All protein components, recognition mechanisms, and catalytic steps have been validated against primary research including crystallographic structures. The model represents the paradigm for prokaryotic NER, a pathway essential for survival after UV exposure and conserved across bacteria.",
